This piece is ascribed to Seneca by ancient tradition3 it is impossible to prove that it is his, and impossible to prove that it is not. The matter will probably con- tinne to be deeided by every one according to his view of Seneca's character and abilities: in the mat- ters of style and of sentiment much may be said on both sides.
